The code defines a memoized Fibonacci implementation using TypeScript bigint for arbitrary precision. The fibonacci function computes the nth Fibonacci number recursively with a FibCache lookup table seeded with base cases 0 and 1, throwing a RangeError for negative indices. The fibSequence function returns an array of the first N Fibonacci numbers by mapping indices through fibonacci. The isFibonacci function tests whether a given bigint is a Fibonacci number by iterating the sequence until reaching or exceeding the target value.